  "text": "Hypertension is known to be a major risk factor for DR and DME. In the Wisconsin Epidemiological Study of Diabetic Retinopathy (WESDR) progression of retinopathy was associated with higher diastolic blood pressure at baseline and an increase in diastolic blood pressure over a 4-year follow-up period [CITATION_1] . Thus, blood pressure control could concurs to prevent and slow down DR development.",
